column5: or worse, Linc's got him!!!!!!
Flossin' with marshmallows again, huh?
I got him AND his light saber.  I see the marshmallow - but what's that white stuff it's stuck to Geoff's face with?  You don't wanna sleep with the pigeons.  Or the guys in the 6-man cabin.
before i call the bookie, whats the odd's on geoff doing the same thing next year?
I hope that white stuff is marshmellow.

I didn't want to highjack FishnSleds excellent report from our adventures at Perfect Vue this past weekend, so here is the PG 13 version of some folks mis-adventures at the Vue.  This pic shows two strangers getting to know each other... personally, if I had a name like YoungOne, I'd have stayed clear of the big guy (Bitsmith)!  Here they are making plans for later after everyone else passed out! Here they are showing off the "tools of the trade" Armageddon!  Here's two old buggers doing their best to find the bottom of a vodka bottle, the whole time watching and learning the art of the take down, from Bitsmith!  The Dr. Mellow even hooked this big guy!  Never and I do mean NEVER pass out in a room full of guys!!!! Gerritt had fun!LOL Thanks for lookin... HH  PS... GBW, the guys in the cabin over a few from us, want your phone number!!!!!
Oh SNAP!!!!!  That's not me, I was "drugged" I swear!  Damn fish-whistle's!!
Armageddon Armageddon Armageddon
looks like you guys had fun    but  why when looking at the pictures, I think I can faintly hear a banjo in the background and Bert Reynolds comes to mind..........
he's got a purdy mouth!!
That was the weekend theme song Terry! HH
LOL at the mello pics.
lol, the mello pics remind me of this little bit from a Dave Chappelle stand up act re: falling asleep around a bunch guys...
Whatever happened to "What happens at Perfect Vue, stays at Perfect Vue"???:rofl2:
Awww, so sorry we didn't stay in your room
HEY GBW    Nudge nudge wink wink. You goin next year too.
LOL.. ya... ive seen that before....
I was not the one to blame this time! I just carried it out! LOL
Someone put too much mustard on my mustard sandwich! HH
Hahahahahahaaaaaa!
for the record, it was a cold cut combo and when I said a bit more mustard, she went to town!

"Geoff complains so much that he complained there was too much mustard on his mustard sandwich" Bitsmith2k circa November 20th 2010  But Shhhh... Geoff was not awake for this momentous proverb. Nor do we think he still understands it's significance.   :rofl2:
yes he does, and yes he said that....
you...you... yes I was awake for that.  same with the whole helicopter thing someone's gonna get a hurt here... Armageddon
Armageddon! Corn!
you pay now!!!!!
What happened to YoungOne?? Still having nightmares I guess....
I was thinking the same thing!
maybe bitsmith's got him!?!?!?!  Insert ball-gag joke here...
